This paper discusses the optimal design of neural reservoirs, which are a type of neural network used for computation. The focus is on the capacity of these reservoirs to store and process information, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of neural engineering (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques to optimize the design of these reservoirs, which is relevant to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also touches on the control and optimization of dynamical systems, which is relevant to the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of information theory to analyze the performance of these reservoirs, which is relevant to the subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
